    "**3. Two players, row (R) and column (C), play against each other. Each of them has a coin. Each player can choose to show “heads” (H) or “tails” (T) of the coin. They have to show their coin simultaneously to the opponent. The row player wins whenever the two coins turn out to be the same sides, either both “heads” or both “tails”. And the\n",
    "column player wins whenever the two coins take different sides. The payoff matrix is**\n",
    "<img src=\"2.png\" style=\"width:400px\"/>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "addressed-alexander",
