   "source": [
    "**4.Two factories, 1 and 2, in a small town both emits some hazardous air pollution. Both factories simultaneously choose the quantity of outputs, $q_i$ for $i = 1, 2$, which bring them more profit for $i$, $\\pi_i = \\ln(q_i) + 2$, as well as more hazardous pollution that hurts both factories, $h_i(q_i, q_{−i}) = q_i + q_{−i}$, where subscript $−i$ denotes the other player. We assume that each factory’s utility is the profit net of of the disutility from pollution, i.e. their payoffs are$$v_i(q_i, q_{−i}) = \\pi_i(q_i) − h_i(q_i, q_{−i}).$$**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "studied-adult",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**(a) For factory $i$, find the best response $q^{*}_{i}$ given the belief that the other factory produces $\\hat{q}_{−i}$.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "helpful-inclusion",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The necessary first-order condition that defines the player’s best response $q_{i}^{*}(\\hat{q}_{-i})$ given her belief about the opponent’s strategy is \n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "    \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial q^{*}_{i}}v_i(q_i^{*}, \\hat{q}_{−i})=\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial q^{*}_{i}}[ (\\ln{q_i^{*}}+2)-(q_i^{*}+\\hat{q}_{-i})]&=0\\\\\n",
    "    \\frac{1}{q_i^{*}}-1&=0\\\\\n",
    "    q_i^{*}&=1\n",
    "\\end{align}\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, the best response $q^{*}_{i}$ given the belief that the other factory produces $\\hat{q}_{−i}$ is $1$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "trained-nurse",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**(b) Is there a dominant strategy for each factory? Briefly explain.**"
