  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "hindu-determination",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**(d) (central planning case) If there is a town government whose interest is to maximize the joint payoff of both factories, $v_1 + v_2$. And assume that the government can enforce an output restrictions on how much each firm produce, what is the optimal output levels $q^m_1$ and $q^m_2$ that the government will mandate?**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "abstract-subscriber",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The total payoff function becomes: \n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "    v_1+v_2&=\\pi_i(q_i)+\\pi_i(q_{-i})−2h_i(q_i, q_{−i})\\\\\n",
    "    &=\\ln(q_i)+\\ln(q_{-i})+4-2(q_i+q_{-i})\n",
    "\\end{align}\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose the government mandate an optimal level of $q^{m}=q_1^{m}=q_2^{m}$, then we have the first order condition as:\n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "    \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial q^m}(v_1+v_2)=2\\ln(q^m)+4-4q^m&=0\\\\\n",
    "    \\frac{2}{q^m}-4&=0\\\\ \n",
    "    q^m&=\\frac{1}{2}\n",
    "\\end{align}\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, the optimal output level the government will mandate is $q^{m}=q_1^{m}=q_2^{m}=\\frac{1}{2}.$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "every-judgment",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**(e) Compare the N.E. outcome with the central planning outcome, specifically**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "macro-sodium",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. how much total pollution is generated in the N.E case vs. the central planning case?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "affecting-bankruptcy",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$h_i(q_i^{*}, q_{−i}^{*})=q_i^{*}+q_{-i}^{*}=1+1=2$$\n",
    "$$h_i(q_i^{m}, q_{−i}^{m})=q_i^{m}+q_{-i}^{m}=\\frac{1}{2}+\\frac{1}{2}=1$$\n",
    "\n",
    "So in the N.E case we have a total pollution of 2 units, whereas in the central planning case we have 1 unit."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "unauthorized-legislature",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2. how much are the payoffs for each factory under the N.E. case vs. the central planning case?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "selected-southeast",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$$v_i(q_{i,-i}^*)=\\ln{q_{i,-i}^*}+2-h_i(q_i^{*}, q_{−i}^{*})=ln(1)+2-2=0$$\n",
    "$$v_i(q_{i,-i}^m)=\\ln{q_{i,-i}^m}+2-h_i(q_i^{m}, q_{−i}^{m})=ln(\\frac{1}{2})+2-1=0.307$$\n",
    "\n",
    "So in the N.E case each factory has a payoff of 0, whereas in the central planning case each factory has a payoff of 0.307."
   ]
  },
